latestPosts.caption:
#TheBeltEdit: I didn’t grow up thinking belts were cool. They were always that annoying afterthought your jeans needed. But then I found these.

Chunky leather, sun stamped studs, vintage conchos, wild shapes. The kind of belts that don’t just sit on your waist, they change your posture, your vibe, your whole energy.

I’ve worn them with denim co ords, lacy dresses, casual joggers, and even basics like a tank top, and every time, they’ve completely flipped the mood.

This edit is a little bit of my archive, a little bit of experimentation, and a lot of fun. Proof that the right belt doesn’t follow the outfit. It leads it. 🤍
